name: Giant Burger
directions: Single User, Locking, Unisex. Restroom is behind the register in the diner area.
comment: Presumably for customers only, the staff was happy to provide me with the key.

name: The Morning Owl
directions: At the back of the coffee house, by the brick wall. Large, clean, unisex bathroom.
comment: I don't think you have to be a paying customer to use the bathroom, but they do make delicious drinks. There are board games, books, magazines inside to browse and relax for a bit. Sometimes the staff will greet a group by saying "Hi guys!", but it's meant (I asked) in a gender neutral way.

name: Living water acupuncture
directions: Down the hall to the left, last door on the right.
comment: Just act like you own the place.

name: Camosun College Student Society - Lansdowne Campus
directions: Ground floor of Richmond House (off Richmond Rd. near Argyle Av.) Turn right from the main door; just past the stairs next to the Pride office is a bathroom with an accordion door.

name: Battlefield Tire Pros
directions: Up the stairway at the end of the hall in our waiting room inside front office
comment: Visit as you wish no purchase needed =]

name: Big Blue Marble Bookstore
directions: Third floor.
comment: Includes changing table. Diapers available depending on whether other customers have brought in extras. Not necessary to be a customer, but supporting local businesses is always appreciated.

name: Caf√© du Monde
directions: Beside the kitchen inside.
comment: Two full single private bathrooms behind a door, one marked women one marked unisex, but with door closed behind you, no one will see which you go in. Sanitation is awful.

name: Coldstone Creamery
directions: straight to the back and to the right
comment: bathroom is marked for both men/women to use

name: 26 Putney School Rd, Putney, VT 05346, USA
directions: In every building at this school there are gender neutral restrooms and single stalled restrooms.
comment: You have to be a student, staff member, or visitor to use said restrooms.

name: The Grand Theater
directions: on the right side of the front lobby
comment: Just walk in and it's directly to the right!

name: B-Side Lounge
directions: Near the dooron the left

name: Southbury Public Library
directions: On second floor in children's department. By the kids movies and new books section. Two separate unisex bathrooms with dark red doors.
comment: Staff might say hi or ask if they can help you. You can say you're just looking around or looking at the movies or going to the bathroom.

name: TRATA
directions: The bathroom on the second floor is a unisex, stalled bathroom.
comment: For paying customers.

name: Bar 209
directions: Towards back bar on right

name: Meijer
directions: Food enterence to the left

name: Oak Hall
directions: On the first floor of the south wing (side furthest from Fairfield Way) next to the other restrooms

name: Salt and Pepper
directions: In the back
comment: Must be a paying customer

name: Pub 32
directions: Next to the bar
comment: May have to be 21+ on certain bar nights

name: McLadden's
directions: In the back toward the right; next to the women's bathroom

name: Starbucks
directions: Inside the main entrance on the right.
comment: Two single-occupant bathrooms with standard "Restroom" signs with braille.  No key or code to get in.  Bathrooms have handrails and space to maneuver a wheelchair.  There is one van-accessible handicap spot close to the door.  All the doors are manual swinging doors.

name: Partridge Creek Mall
directions: Near the Sketchers store with the blue awning.
comment: Family bathrooms with 2 single stalls.

name: Lansdowne Branch Library
directions: Ask at the Information Desk for the key!

name: Blick Art Materials
directions: Back left corner
comment: It's fine to come in only to use the restroom, any associate will be happy to tell you where it is if you ask.

name: Massachusetts College of Liberal Arts
comment: Most on-campus buildings have gender neutral facilities or single unisex stalls.  All accessible!

name: Robert Carr Chapel, TCU and Brite Divinity School
directions: The bathroom is in the foyer.

name: Nell A. and W. Oliver Harrison Building
directions: The Harrison building sits behind the Brite/TCU Chapel. There are two single stall gender neutral restrooms in this building. The first is on the second floor close to the elevator. The second is inside the executive suite on the 3rd floor.

name: Route 66 Grille
comment: Customers only

name: 101-125 US-71 BUS, Butler, MO 64730, USA
directions: NW corner of bakery/deli. Look left when you walk in door.
comment: Might be better if you buy a drink or donut, but it's probably not required.

name: Sussex Court
directions: Directly to the left of the front entrance.

name: One World Brewing
directions: One World Brewery is located below Farm Burger. Entrance is through the alley between Farm Burger and Salsa's. Both of their single-stall restrooms, which are located on the far side of the bar, are all-gender.

name: Bahen Centre for Information Technology
directions: Through the front door (St. George Street entrance), take the second right. The single-stall washrooms will be on your left.

name: Bahen Centre for Information Technology
directions: Through the front door (St. George Street entrance), take the second right. The single-stall washrooms will be on your left.

name: Hart House
directions: Across from the Great Hall

name: Hart House
directions: Across from the Great Hall

name: Ingles Gas Express
directions: The restroom is on the left of the entrance

name: Health South Rehabilitation Hospital
directions: End of the hall to the left near the nurse station.
comment: You may have to sign in at the front desk. Just pick a random room number i.e. 208B

name: 14034-14054 Palawan Way, Marina Del Rey, CA 90292, USA
directions: Outside of Del Rey Yacht Club
comment: Not locked

name: Tierra Mia Coffee
comment: You have to be a paying customer and ask for the key.

name: Jo Ann and Wayne Moore Building, Brite Divinity School
directions: Third floor of this building

name: McKinney
directions: At the top of the stairs, veer slightly right past the cafe (on your right), past the first meeting room (also on your right) and down the hall toward the pool and Ping-Pong tables. You'll see the Everyone restrooms on the left.
comment: You must be let into the building or have a security pass.

name: Safeway
directions: Enter the store and take an immediate left toward the in-store Starbucks. The restrooms are in the back of the cafe.

name: Hood College
directions: Third floor, the side the stairs are on
comment: It is a non-gendered single stall bathroom I've used countless times. Just be warned the elevator to get to the third floor is quite old and may not be able to fit electric scooters or larger electric wheelchairs

name: UCA Student Health
directions: First floor, as soon as you walk in the front. Also on the third floor by the elevators. Possibly on the 22nd floor as well.

name: Costa Coffee
directions: Back of the shop on the right, 2 stalls both with locks and sinks.
comment: For paying customers but I think you can use it either way.

name: Walmart Supercenter
directions: Back of the store, by shoe dept.
comment: Door is usually closed, knock first.

name: Hot Toddies pub & grub
directions: Reg bathrooms but bar is transgender friendly

name: UCC Campus(Boole Basement)
directions: Just before the gendered bathrooms, inside is like a disabled toilets but door is clearly marked

name: Sage Caf√©
directions: The main restroom, down the hall, behind the kitchen
comment: The staff seems very laid back, so I don't think they'd mind non-customer use? The place is small, though, so it may be more difficult to be subtle/discreet.

name: Tazy's Burgers and Grill
comment: All are welcome!

name: 111 New St, Decatur, GA 30030, USA
directions: Next to Decatur healing arts
comment: only for customers of businesses/restaurants in the complex. Ask for the key as they are kept locked. There are two single-occupancy bathrooms available, both accessible by ramp from either level

name: Asheville Raven & Crone
directions: Back room on the left.
comment: Complimentary tea is available. Say hello to the shop cat Lovey.

name: Rise Above
directions: Not accessible as is at the top of a flight of stairs

name: Niagara Artists Centre
comment:
Have paid events most evenings, but are free to the public during their gallery hours which are:
Wed 10 AM - 5 PM
Thurs 10 AM - 5 PM
Fri 10 AM - 5 PM
Sat 12 NOON - 4 PM

name: McCool's Ice Cream and Coffee Bar
directions: In the back of the store, near the back door.
comment: You have to be a paying customer. Very small bathroom but usually pretty clean.

name: Roji tea lounge
comment: This is a great place to get a drink and hang out for awhile. Free wifi, and a gender neutral bathroom.

name: Think Coffee
directions: Two-thirds of the way back, just past the barista station, on the right.
comment: I haven't ever tried to use the restroom here without buying something, so I don't know how much of a fuss they'd kick up about it if you didn't.

name: Indian River Mall
directions: Restrooms by food court include a "family" stall.

name: Majestic 11 Cinema
directions: "Family" stall at the end of main hallway. Located by theatre #6. Has private toilet, sink, and changing table. Door has a secure lock.
comment: Staff are friendly and will assist anyone who is being harassed! (Entry made by LGBT cinema staff member!)

name: Geek Bar Beta
directions: First floor, in the back to the right. If I remember correctly, their restrooms are gendered, but there is a sign that explicitly states that you're welcome in either room.

name: Chandler-Gilbert Community College
directions: Ironwood building (North end) has a single-stall restroom.

name: Blacks Creek - Eastbound
street: I-84 rest area at mile marker 62
directions: In rest area building
comment: 2 total: 1 on either side of hall between men's and women's restrooms. Single occupancy restroom with locking door and lots of room

name: The Mall at Johnson City
directions: Bottom floor/lower level in food court.
comment: Two family-style restrooms are available right past the gendered restrooms.

name: H-E-B
directions: At the front of the store where a sign marks restrooms, to your right after making a turn into the hallway.
comment: Single stall, lockable

name: Trader Joe's
directions: Straight towards the back.

name: Cosi
directions: In back of restaurant next to check out.
comment: 2 single stalls, both unisex. No purchase needed.

name: Spinal Decompression & Chiropractic Center
comment: You don't have to be a patient. Just give a slightly pained smile, cross your legs and say please. :o)

name: Comic Envy
directions: Blue door painted like tardis. Please feel free to ask at register!

name: Target
comment: Family restroom but also serves as gender neutral restroom.

name: Optimystical Studios
directions: On the Ivanhoe side of the Marvel 29 building, across the street from Burgerville.
comment: Just ask to use the bathroom.

name: Harlow College
directions: Building C next to the hair salon

name: Roberts Bestway
directions: Back corner on the left.

name: The Front Room at The Wharf
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Walmart
directions: In the back by the shoe section. To the right of electronics.
comment: Family bathroom in back of store

name: Naab Caf√©
directions: Locking single user

name: Calibasil Vietnamese Eatery
comment: Close to Rt. 128 exit 20.

name: Chipotle Mexican Grill
directions: Rear left

name: Dunkin' Donuts
comment: Close to Rt. 128, exit 24

name: The Green Room in The Black Box
directions: Two bathrooms, one is accessible, one is not. Both are gender neutral. When you go into the Green Room the toilets are beside the bar on the far wall.
comment: Only the Green Room has specificallygender neutral toilets. In the Black Box main room, there is an accessible toilet but it isn't specifically gender neutral.

name: Student Center-Wayne State University
directions: 1st floor of the Student Center

name: Park West Dental Care
comment: very nice staff

name: McCabe Library (Swarthmore College)
directions: Second level of the building

name: University of New Mexico Student Health and Counseling Center
directions: One large single-stall right as you walk in, another right around the corner. There are more upstairs if those are full.
comment: The workers here have had safe space training and are happy to help or give directions. Restrooms are available to everyone.

name: New Mexico Museum of Natural History and Science
directions: Take a right before reaching the planet area. Go all the way down the white hallway and to the right, it's next to the security office.
comment: It's generally not accessible to the public other than teachers, but if you act like you know where you're going no one will stop you. If they do you might need to explain, but this is generally a trans-friendly workplace. Must pay museum admission, but they might let you in if you explain your situation.
